2 Months Ago “He has disappointed the court,” he ruled. Justice Abang, who refused to grant Maina’s application for an order directing the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission to release his confiscated property, including a BMW car, also dismissed his request for an order to set aside the November 18 and December 4, 2020 orders. The court on November 18, 2020, ordered the trial of Maina in absentia after he jumped bail. Also on December 4, 2020, the court ordered Maina to be remanded in prison custody pending the hearing and final determination of his matter.



